    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Chat Template Handler\n\n**Only file modified:** `common/chat.cpp`\n\n### Two changes:\n\n**1. New static handler function** (inserted after `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`, before `namespace workaround` ~line 1519):\n\n```cpp\nstatic common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(\n        const common_chat_template & tmpl,\n        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {\n    // iterates inputs.messages, collects system content,\n    // builds prompt using [INST]/[/INST] wrapping + bos_token()/eos_token()\n    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;\n    return data;\n}\n```\n\nPrompt format produced:\n- `<s>[INST] {system}\\n{user1} [/INST] {assistant1}</s>[INST] {user2} [/INST]`\n\n**2. Detection block** (inserted just before `return std::nullopt;` at line 1690):\n\n```cpp\nif (src.find(\"[INST]\") != std::string::npos &&\n    src.find(\"[/INST]\") != std::string::npos &&\n    src.find(\"[SYSTEM_PROMPT]\") == std::string::npos) {\n    LOG_DBG(\"Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\\n\");\n    return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);\n}\n```\n\nThe `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absence check ensures no conflict with the existing Ministral 3 handler (which also uses Mistral-family `[INST]` tokens). No changes to `chat.h` — `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` already exists.",
